## Phase 3: Refactor Installer - Inject artifactsDir

### WHY
Currently Installer.phase3WalkArtifacts() hardcodes path.join(projectDir, 'artifacts'). After migration, artifactsDir must be injectable so init.ts can pass a downloaded temp path or local path.

### WHAT
Modify `src/domains/installation/installer.ts`:

#### Changes to install() method
Add artifactsDir to options:
```javascript
async install(options = {}) {
  const {
    directory: projectDir,
    ides,
    artifactsDir,  // NEW: injected instead of hardcoded
    autoConfirm,
  } = options;
  // REMOVE: const artifactsDir = path.join(projectDir, 'artifacts');
```

#### Changes to phase3WalkArtifacts()
Update signature to accept artifactsDir:
```javascript
async phase3WalkArtifacts(artifactsDir, config) {
  // artifactsDir is now passed in - no more path.join(projectDir, 'artifacts')
}
```

#### Changes to phase1CollectConfig()
Update to use artifactsDir for module.yaml:
```javascript
async phase1CollectConfig(projectDir, artifactsDir) {
  const modulePath = path.join(artifactsDir, 'module.yaml');
  // NEVER fallback to projectDir/artifacts - that would be confusing in production
}
```

### NO CHANGES NEEDED
- uninstall.ts - reads _qd/ manifest only, NOT artifacts/
- status.ts - reads _qd/ manifest only, NOT artifacts/
- phase4CopyToTargets, phase6WriteManifest, phaseAddToGitignore - unchanged

### TEST OBLIGATIONS
- artifactsDir is passed correctly from init.ts
- phase3WalkArtifacts uses passed artifactsDir (not hardcoded)
- phase1CollectConfig reads module.yaml from artifactsDir (not projectDir/artifacts)
- Existing init flow still works after refactor
